    {
      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "As a consequence of a strong wind from northwesterly directions, large wind slabs formed. They must be evaluated with care and prudence. Single winter sport participants can release avalanches in some places, caution is to be exercised in particular at transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack, when entering gullies and bowls for example. In particular here the avalanches can be released in the old snow and reach quite a large size. <br/> With the freezing level at 2600 metres, combined with the foehn wind and solar radiation, some wet and moist avalanches are still possible at medium mountain altitudes on slopes that have not yet been completely cleared in recent days. <br/> Backcountry touring and other off-piste activities call for experience in the assessment of avalanche danger and caution. Careful route selection is recommended.",
        "highlights": "Fresh wind slabs represent the main danger. The danger of moist and wet avalanches will increase during the day."
